=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lorinnor>Lorinnor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/11/02 10:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Wizard snaring in GROUPS !?!?</span><hr size=1> I've got about 140 days /p on my Ranger, to lvl 54 only because I don't care much for the race to 60. I can find fun in other ways, and I don't think that makes me incompetent.<br>
I duo quite a bit with a wizard. Never does she have snare even memmed then.  That sort of aggro is the last thing I'd want on her, damage does enough of it.<br>
I couldn't think of many situations where I'd want a wizard to snare in a group, since its an AE. I'd rely on a pally or whoever to stun them as they turn to run much rather, makes for much better control, as long as it's single target.<br>
Someone saying wizards get groups because they can snare just plain baffles me. In my book, a wizard snaring is about the very last resort before letting a mob run. Most of the time a well-timed nuke to finish off instead would be preferable. <br>
Or am I missing anything here?<br>
<br>
Lorinnor Gil-Forn<br>
54 Ranger<br>
Solusek Ro server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=madai>Madai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/12/02 4:03 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Damage Dealer Balance Problem</span><hr size=1> Okay, I jumped on this thread late, but I have an answer making wizards desire a group.  give them a single target direct damage nuke with efficiency based on the yellow bars of group members.  For example, the level 60 version of such a spell would do 2k damage for 300 mana in a full group with full stamina bars, and drain the equivalent of jumping three times.  if the wizard cast this spell without a group... 333 damage :P.  If everyone in the group is exhausted... 0 damage.<br>
<br>
the spell efect could be something like<br>
<br>
A disturbance of mana in the region exhausts you.  This also makes the invigor spells actually have a use as well.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=siryakk>Sir Yakk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 152<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/13/02 10:41 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Damage Dealer Balance Problem</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>he ability to kill LOW HPS, HIGH DPS mobs very quickly. And the existence of these mobs is really up to the Level Designer. How would you wizard-types feel if each zone had various mob types that were melee-centric, ie, a lot of HPS and moderate melee output. However there should always (in my opinion) be much NASTIER mobs, with fairly low hit points, that are intended for the Nuker-Types to burn down. Killing these with tanks would be very inefficient; rather, wizards burning them down would take very little effort and require a heck of a lot less healing.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
*nod*, but once you start grinding those mobs and get high uptime, wizards return to the previous utility.  There needs to be such mobs mixed in with normal mobs -- so, the focusing abilities of wizard DPH can be brought to bear.<br>
<br>
If you have a zone full of low HP high DPS mobs, and you are managing a high engagement rate, the wizard has issues.  Take the same zone, and make 20% of the mobs have 1/2 the HPs and 5 x the damage output, and not avoidable while doing the normal stuff (and vice versa).<br>
<br>
The wizards would hate killing the low-DPS high-HP mobs.  The tanks would hate killing the high-DPS low-HP mobs.  Get some of each in a group, and both gain advantages<br>
<br>
And, as noted, caster mobs don't work -- first, caster mobs do less DPS than melee often, are often easy to neutralize (just stun/tap/bash/resist them). . .  And, they often do their damage to the puller rather than to the tank.<br>
<br>
So yes, you could fix wizards by changing the environment rather than changing wizards.<br>
